ENTRY            13650   20260313   20260508   20260508       1528
SUBENT        13650001   20260313   20260508   20260508       1528
BIB                 12         42
TITLE      Measurement of the (n,H3) Cross Section in Nitrogen
           and Its Relationship to the Tritium Production in the
           Atmosphere
AUTHOR     (E.L.Fireman)
REFERENCE  (J,PR,91,922,1953)
           #doi:10.1103/PhysRev.91.922
INSTITUTE  (1USABNL)
FACILITY   (REAC,1USABNL) The fission plate facility of the
           Brookhaven reactor.
INC-SOURCE Fast neutrons from 235U fission plate.
DETECTOR   (GEMUC,IOCH) Geiger counter and the cloud chamber.
SAMPLE     Stainless steel container filled with mixture of
           nitrogen and hydrogen, or nitrogen, hydrogen, and
           ammonia.
METHOD     (EXTB,CHSEP) The stainless steel container was placed
           in the fission plate facility. Most irradiations were
           done with a 50-50 mixture of nitrogen and hydrogen.
           The gas is irradiated for four or five days; the
           container is not very radioactive upon removal so no
           special handling precautions are necessary. The gas
           is emptied directly from the container into an
           expansion cloud chamber of 10-liter volume or into a
           Bask connected to a palladium thimble and counter
           filling system. In the 119-hour irradiation, the
           mixture is let into the cloud chamber by bubbling
           through a water tower. Titration of the water with
           HC1 showed 99 percent of the NH3 to be trapped in the
           water. In the 140-hour irradiation, the mixture
           passes first through a liquid air trap and then
           through a water tower into the chamber. Titration
           showed 99 percent of the NH3 to be taken out in the
           liquid air trap. This trapped NH3 is later decomposed
           over hot Mg, passed through palladium, and put into a
           Geiger counter.
MONITOR    ((MONIT1)16-S-32(N,P)15-P-32,,SIG,,FIS)
           ((MONIT2)12-MG-24(N,P)11-NA-24,,SIG,,FIS)
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information on sources of uncertainties.
HISTORY    (19970416C)
           (20260313A) BP: Updated to new date formats, lower
                      case. Corrections according last EXFOR rules
                       and Dict. Added FACILITY, METHOD, doi,
                      individual irradiations.
ENDBIB              42
COMMON               3          3
KT-DUMMY   MONIT1     MONIT2
MEV        MB         MB
       1.32       50.0        1.0
ENDCOMMON            3
